Which response did you need to hear the most? Let me know in the comments :)

Friday night live with warikoo 

23 Sep 2022

Oh, how times have changed! From love letters to dedicating posts, and travelling for hours to meet each other to being together virtually 24/7!

Really enjoyed this lively performance and I’m sure you will too :))

@yugmofficial

What we should know about money is unfortunately totally different from what we were taught.

How you think of money, especially in your 20s, is fundamental to building your worldview. 
Often, we realise this much later in life. Imagine how wiser money decisions you'd make if you knew better!

The most inspiring people I know are the most honest ones.

When life doesn’t go their way, they go with the way of life.

In doing so, more often than not, life ends up creating a way for them. 
Isn’t that the most liberating thing that could happen?

Snippets from my favourite part of the week, from talking with you all!

And also, some wonderful life questions answered, again thanks to you all :)

On that note, what should be the topic of my next AMA?

Friday night live with warikoo 

16th September 2022

There is no "right time".
You do not "have to get there soon".
There are no norms that you must follow, to be called successful.

Success is a relationship you have with yourself, and you get to decide when do you want to do whatever you want to do.

It turns out, you get the maximum success when you let go of the plans crafted by the world and go create your own world - because, hey, it's YOUR world!

Even I hate the current education system! 

However, if you are wondering whether you should drop out of college or not, this video will not only give you the answer you are looking for, rather also let you make the best of your college life.

Not a random dude on the internet.
Not the relative who calls your parents to question you.
Not the girl or guy you are envious of, on Instagram.

YOU will change your life.
And that is more than enough.
In conversation with @adamgrant and his latest book Think Again.
